#Here we have iterated through all the numerical columns and if there are any special characters, we consider them as missing values and
#replace them with zero.
#After every value is replaced with zero, we run another loop to replace the value with mean of the appropriate column.

#We have not used mean in first loop because while calculating the mean, it will through an error as it will encounter the special character
#in the column.

for y in df_c.columns:
  for x in df_c[y]:
    if (x=="?")|(x=="_")|(x=='-')|(x=='!')|(x=='*')|(x=='$')|(x=='#')|(x=='@')|(x=='%')|(x=='^')|(x=='&')|(x=='~')|(x=='`')|(x==':')|(x==';'):
      df_c[y].replace(x,0,inplace=True)

for y in df_c.columns:
  for x in df_c[y]:
    if x==0:
      df_c[y].replace(x,df_c[y].mean(),inplace=True)

In [21]:
#Creating a range of 2 to 10. Creating an empty list.
clusters = range(2,11)
mean_distortions = []

#we are creating a KMeans model. We are iterating it using for loop from 2 to 10 clusters.
#After fitting the model, we have predicted the model. We have used scaled dataset for better predictions.
#We are appending the average of all the distances of data points from their respective clusters in the list.
#We have use cdist function to calculate the distances. 
for k in clusters:
  model = KMeans(n_clusters=k)
  model.fit(df_scaled)
  pred = model.predict(df_scaled)
  mean_distortions.append(sum(np.min(cdist(df_scaled,model.cluster_centers_,'euclidean'),axis=1))/df_scaled.shape[0])
In [22]:
#We are using plt.plot for plotting the k and mean_distortions
#We will find the optimal k using elbow method.

plt.plot(clusters,mean_distortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average Distortions')
plt.title('Finding the optimal value of k using elbow method.')

print("Assumptions/Prerequisite of PCA :\n\nThere should be linearity in the dataset. The variable combine in a linear manner to form a dataset.")
print("The importance of mean and covariance, i.e. there is no guarantee that the directions of maximum variance will contain \ngood features for discrimination.")
print("It assumes that the principal component with high variance must be paid attention and the principal component with lower variance \nare disregarded as noise.")

Assumptions/Prerequisite of PCA :

There should be linearity in the dataset. The variable combine in a linear manner to form a dataset.
The importance of mean and covariance, i.e. there is no guarantee that the directions of maximum variance will contain 
good features for discrimination.
It assumes that the principal component with high variance must be paid attention and the principal component with lower variance 
are disregarded as noise.
In [62]:
print("Advantages : \n\nRemoves Multi-collinearity,i.e. it removes correlated features.\nIt makes the variables independent of each other.")
print("It decreases the computational time as we have less dimensions.")
print("It improves the performance of algorithms.\nIt makes visualization easier with less no. of dimensions.")
print("It reduces overfitting.\nIt avoids curse of dimensionality.\nIt decreases the storage requirement.\n")

print("Disadvantages : \n\nIndependent variables become less interpretable.")
print("Data Standaradization is must before PCA, otherwise it will not be able to find optimal Principal Components.")

Advantages : 

Removes Multi-collinearity,i.e. it removes correlated features.
It makes the variables independent of each other.
It decreases the computational time as we have less dimensions.
It improves the performance of algorithms.
It makes visualization easier with less no. of dimensions.
It reduces overfitting.
It avoids curse of dimensionality.
It decreases the storage requirement.

Disadvantages : 

Independent variables become less interpretable.
Data Standaradization is must before PCA, otherwise it will not be able to find optimal Principal Components.
